cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.MA, cs.SE

This paper is about a programming method for designing agents that reason logically about their actions and sensor information in the presence of incomplete knowledge. This topic falls under the field of artificial intelligence (AI), which is why cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses a system of Constraint Handling Rules, which is a formalism used in logic programming (cs.PL) and constraint programming (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper discusses the formal semantics for the constraint solver, which is related to the field of logic (cs.LO). Finally, the paper discusses how agents control their own behavior, which is related to the field of software engineering (cs.SE).
